WEBVTT

00:00.066 --> 00:00.567
Let's do this.

00:00.607 --> 00:24.416
If this is your first vision Sunday, what happens now is that I spend the next little while talking about everything that God has done in the life of the church in this last calendar year and then Nikki will come up and she will share the vision that God has downloaded to us both for the coming year.

00:25.117 --> 00:29.522
So normally, I have to go on double speed now.

00:29.826 --> 00:35.873
I have to go on double speed so you know when you listen to some people's messages they're a bit slow so you just like times one and a half times two.

00:37.034 --> 00:38.316
This is going to be at times two.

00:38.976 --> 00:42.220
Last year I went for 25 minutes so I've practiced three times so far.

00:42.240 --> 00:43.642
My best time is 12 and a half.

00:43.842 --> 00:45.964
I am absolutely powering through.

00:45.984 --> 00:48.847
I've been chopping loads of bits out too but it's all there.

00:49.248 --> 00:49.929
It's going to be good.

00:49.969 --> 00:52.472
Are you ready for sort of, let's say 13 because you always clap.

00:52.512 --> 00:53.252
Let's go for 14.

00:53.553 --> 00:54.674
But we're going to

00:55.042 --> 01:01.682
We are going to have a look at the altar of thanksgiving for everything that God has done in us and through us this year.

01:01.986 --> 01:04.108
Let's go, early years, little ones.

01:04.188 --> 01:15.157
It continues to run here every Thursday morning and this year we have welcomed parents and carers, grandparents, child minders and expectant moms, along with children from birth to school age into this building.

01:15.177 --> 01:23.845
The children enjoy play and creativity, stories, singing and snacks and the grown-ups are met with bottomless hot drinks, breakfast bars, conversation and support.

01:24.165 --> 01:31.972
And what has been really beautiful this year is seeing families take ownership of the group, offering ideas, caring for one another and requesting prayer.

01:31.952 --> 01:43.211
The vast majority of those who come here don't come to skylike on a Sunday, but they do leave knowing that they are safe here, that they are valued, they're deeply loved by a team who simply want to share the heart of Jesus with them.

01:43.972 --> 01:44.634
Woo!

01:44.654 --> 01:45.114
Belong!

01:45.455 --> 01:45.936
Keep it short.

01:46.517 --> 01:47.939
It's a three-second-clap max.

01:48.320 --> 01:48.941
De-de-de-de-dot.

01:50.043 --> 01:51.986
Actually, not three seconds, just out.

01:52.034 --> 01:58.760
Okay, Belong continues to bring together the oldest and the youngest among us over tea, toast and jam.

01:58.960 --> 02:00.461
Sounds good, I'd go for Marmite.

02:00.481 --> 02:10.030
It's packed with singing, stories, sensory play and what happens is laughter wonderfully expected chaos and friendships that cross the generations from the youngest to the oldest.

02:10.390 --> 02:13.332
It's a space that gently says, come as you are, you belong.

02:13.653 --> 02:22.020
This year also saw early years family breakfasts and spontaneous outings creating relaxed no pressure spaces for young families to connect and

02:22.000 --> 02:26.790
We have reimagined the crest where families can gather, build friendships and feel supported.

02:26.830 --> 02:29.575
Seeking with kids, the kids' church continues to flourish.

02:29.856 --> 02:35.026
We now have over 100 children registered with 50 to 60 up there every week.

02:36.194 --> 02:39.417
Thank you for joining in and being part of the team moving forward.

02:39.657 --> 02:46.363
We have seen children engaging deeply in worship upstairs, asking thoughtful questions and growing in their confidence and in their faith.

02:46.383 --> 02:55.090
Over the summer holiday club welcomed 50 children for several days of festival style fun, helping children to discover that they are God's masterpiece, love beyond measure.

02:55.431 --> 03:04.398
Our light party on the 31st of October welcomed 40 kids and their families celebrating Jesus, and this is the way to do it, with inflatables, craft, waffles and play.

03:04.639 --> 03:06.180
That's a good way to celebrate Jesus.

03:06.160 --> 03:10.665
And none of this happens without an incredible team of volunteers who faithfully show up week after week.

03:10.685 --> 03:11.285
They're up there now.

03:11.586 --> 03:14.909
Huge thanks to Leanne and the early years team, Anita and the kids team.

03:15.350 --> 03:16.571
Right, it's time to look at youth.

03:16.891 --> 03:19.014
What a year it has been for Skylar youth.

03:19.054 --> 03:24.219
We have seen growth not just in numbers but in depth of relationships, in confidence and community.

03:24.500 --> 03:29.945
Made possible by an outstanding team who pour in time, creativity, prayer, passion and love.

03:29.965 --> 03:34.711
Tuesday youth continues to be a welcoming space to belong with games, snacks, prayers, toast.

03:34.911 --> 03:36.132
You're hearing the theme here.

03:36.112 --> 03:44.941
to the mix, seeing around 20 young people each week and on Sundays we often have 25 to 30 youth diving deeper into the Bible in interrelationship.

03:45.222 --> 03:56.354
With the addition this year of an older youth group for year 11 and above, youth life group continues as a more intimate space for older youth gathering to chat, pray, read the Bible, do life and have fun together.

03:56.694 --> 04:06.084
This year's youth events have included a pancake party, good, ninja warrior social, even better, taste and see, bonfire nights, Christmas filming, Christmas parties and a weekend away.

04:06.064 --> 04:09.095
And there was loads of things on the list for this year coming, but there isn't time.

04:09.135 --> 04:10.178
There's so much coming.

04:10.519 --> 04:13.691
And here's some feedback from some of the parents to the youth team.

04:14.313 --> 04:15.858
Firstly, we want to say

04:16.386 --> 04:20.011
Thank you for making X feel so welcome at your youth club.

04:20.212 --> 04:22.735
He's absolutely loving it, and he's made some lovely friends.

04:23.196 --> 04:26.441
Another parent said, thank you for all you so into our young people.

04:26.801 --> 04:29.245
It's so important, and I'm so thankful to you and the team.

04:29.585 --> 04:34.593
Another said, thank you so much for all your kindness, support, generosity, and the time that you give to our children.

04:34.613 --> 04:36.015
Thank you, Kate, Joel, the whole youth team.

04:36.035 --> 04:37.036
You guys are epic.

04:37.898 --> 04:38.098
Brilliant.

04:38.818 --> 04:42.829
Senior Gold, from this end to this end, this is the other end of Belong.

04:42.869 --> 04:48.705
Senior Gold provides a space for worship, prayer and fellowship for the older folk in our Skylark family.

04:49.326 --> 04:55.122
This year, they also walk together through loss, remembering dearly-loved members of the fellowship.

04:55.202 --> 05:01.629
Dot Flack passed away in May and Alan Seeger in July, and this team have held each other through those storms.

05:02.229 --> 05:09.116
Mike, who heads it up, writes this, our opening message for the year was from Isaiah 43, forget the former things, do not dwell on the past.

05:09.177 --> 05:11.058
See, I am doing a new thing.

05:11.379 --> 05:19.868
And he said, that was spoken 700 years before Jesus, and it's still speaking to the most aided people in our congregation at this moment.

05:19.888 --> 05:22.130
And they are saying this, how cool is this?

05:22.530 --> 05:27.136
We do not want to let the past hinder us from experiencing God's will in the present.

05:27.576 --> 05:28.958
Come on, senior gold.

05:29.278 --> 05:30.199
You are leading the way.

05:30.260 --> 05:31.701
Thank you, Mike, and the rest of the team.

05:31.761 --> 05:32.182
Amazing.

05:32.602 --> 05:34.645
Our Deaf congregation is going really well.

05:34.685 --> 05:43.195
Val writes that there are generally about 20 people attending from as far as Ipswich and Wheelie, Rayleigh, Billerick, most of them coming from Chelmsford.

05:43.215 --> 05:46.139
And there's also a monthly life group event that's held via Zoom.

05:46.219 --> 05:46.860
Thank you, Val.

05:46.900 --> 05:48.482
Thank you to the signing team.

05:48.902 --> 05:50.024
We love our Deaf Church.

05:50.044 --> 05:51.826
We are so glad you're here with us today.

05:52.418 --> 05:53.179
authentic.

05:53.860 --> 06:00.927
We took 51 men this year from across the church and the network to the late district for an amazing three days of walking and fellowship together.

06:01.088 --> 06:01.808
Woo-hoo!

06:01.828 --> 06:10.978
We had three men's breakfast amended and we focused on real tough topics like grief and mental health and how we can support and encourage each other and men need this stuff.

06:11.239 --> 06:16.885
We also started doing a men's monthly pub night at the Fox and Raven tonight, 7.30, if you fancy coming.

06:16.905 --> 06:17.906
Bismoke!

06:18.082 --> 06:19.744
Every one of the bespoke, woo!

06:20.385 --> 06:27.375
Every one of the bespoke brunches for our women have been a sold out success, literally sold out, with unbelievable food, Christine.

06:27.395 --> 06:34.003
Top conversation, worship, inspiration and fun, and this year also saw the incredible launch of the bespoke collective back in June.

06:34.364 --> 06:41.674
A gathering of over 100 women from across the UK for times of refreshing challenge, relating workshops, TED-style tours, worship and more.

06:41.974 --> 06:44.818
Thank you to everyone involved with bespoke and authentic.

06:47.682 --> 06:52.808
We move on to some very cool stats from our work into the community and our pastoral care.

06:52.969 --> 06:53.629
Are you ready?

06:54.871 --> 06:55.051
Go!

06:55.652 --> 07:00.958
Over 1,100 meals have been cooked and delivered from this place to people in the community.

07:01.479 --> 07:06.025
Over 230 food hampers have been delivered to people in our community.

07:06.045 --> 07:13.554
250 girls have completed the Flourish self-esteem course across five high schools this year.

07:13.890 --> 07:19.136
This year also a boys course has been written and we are ready to launch that into schools later this year.

07:19.517 --> 07:34.294
You'll recall that we are a beacon church standing against domestic abuse and this year 53 victims and survivors of domestic abuse have been supported and also three domestic abuse training days have been delivered to other churches in Chelmsford from here.

07:34.575 --> 07:35.376
That is so cool.

07:35.696 --> 07:40.562
We have run four mental health and wellbeing courses in the prison.

07:40.834 --> 07:44.700
We have supported 300 people through healthcare for the homeless.

07:45.160 --> 07:48.966
We have provided over 500 breakfast bars to a local primary school.

07:49.247 --> 07:53.833
We also have a bursary fund into primary schools where they can apply to us for things.

07:53.893 --> 08:05.010
And this year we have supported more than 12 families across three schools with school uniforms, with coats when it's getting cold, school trips and after school clubs being funded, which is incredible.

08:05.346 --> 08:12.555
We have also sent 66, this is a hard sentence to say, 66 sets of socks and chocks delivered to chess for the homeless.

08:13.116 --> 08:14.277
Yes, it came out.

08:14.498 --> 08:15.419
I'm never doing that again.

08:15.439 --> 08:18.643
There were 12 pamper boxes delivered to the women's refuge.

08:19.084 --> 08:24.390
We did one-to-one bereavement counseling for four students at Chelmsford College, which was so important.

08:24.411 --> 08:30.218
Seven men gave their life to Jesus at Alpha in the prison, and this year we're gonna be running it every single week of the year.

08:30.578 --> 08:33.362
We led six prison services.

08:33.698 --> 08:46.788
On Sundays, we gave every man in terms of a prison a Mars bar, which may seem small, but every 660 Mars bars, given out as Christmas gifts, as part of their Christmas package this year given by us, we have supported people with court cases.

08:47.529 --> 08:48.091
This is cool.

08:48.251 --> 08:49.554
Who knew this?

08:49.602 --> 08:55.887
for people in our community who need it, beds, washing machines, bunk beds, bedding for families in need.

08:56.188 --> 09:05.776
You guys gave over £5,000 into the pastoral offering, which was distributed to people in this room to help them get through Christmas without having as much stress as they may have done.

09:06.096 --> 09:14.363
There have been thousands of hugs, countless pastoral catch-ups, hospital visits, meal trains and many, many meetings that the pastoral team are sitting with you through.

09:14.844 --> 09:19.588
Through partnerships with schools, with the prison, the council, the NHS and local agencies,

09:19.568 --> 09:23.633
Skylark continues to show up with compassion, dignity and love.

09:23.713 --> 09:28.378
Thank you, Eddie, Phil, Julie, Tina, Paula, Christine, Leslie and the huge team who make all of this possible.

09:29.700 --> 09:30.641
Continuing on.

09:32.243 --> 09:34.726
I know, you know normally, as I said, you can double the speed of things.

09:34.746 --> 09:37.209
You can go back and watch this and just half the tempo and it'll be nice.

09:38.010 --> 09:39.151
Nice cup of tea.

09:39.171 --> 09:48.562
Okay, continuing on with Pastoral Care and Counseling, we have run two bereavement courses this year that have offered a safe and compassionate space to grieve and process loss.

09:48.738 --> 10:08.175
Listen to this, our counseling team, which is currently 13 professionally trained volunteers, have supported 58 people voluntarily giving 1,112 hours of professional care, which would equate to approximately 60,000 pounds worth of counseling provision to people in this church and beyond.

10:08.215 --> 10:09.576
How incredible is that?

10:10.077 --> 10:17.263
The prayer chain has faithfully covered over 50 situations, including some life-threatening circumstances and prayers for babies and children.

10:17.303 --> 10:18.724
So thank you to Liz and the

10:18.704 --> 10:22.674
whole pastoral and counselling team.

10:23.298 --> 10:30.304
Raising Larks, which is our adoption fostering special guardianship and kinship care group, is growing and going from strength to strength.

10:30.364 --> 10:43.736
It supports 12 families directly at monthly gatherings and up to 25 families overall through wider connection and families have walked through loads of things together, new arrivals, children returning to their birth families or going to their forever home.

10:44.076 --> 10:47.919
Wherever they are on their journey, they will find understanding, love and belonging.

10:48.280 --> 10:49.100
And this is beautiful.

10:49.200 --> 10:53.284
One child walked in and said they couldn't believe that everyone there was adopted or

10:53.264 --> 10:54.306
just like them.

10:54.686 --> 10:57.891
That sense of not being the only one has been deeply significant.

10:57.931 --> 11:01.176
So thank you, Rach, and the Raising Labs team.

11:01.656 --> 11:05.402
Hospitality continues to be one of the quiet strengths of Skylock.

11:05.702 --> 11:16.178
What might look like simple acts, opening doors, making drinks, sharing meals, has again and again become the place where people first experience welcome belonging and love.

11:16.450 --> 11:18.693
Here is a really powerful example of this.

11:19.113 --> 11:27.184
Someone who walked into the building for the first time was met at the door, was escorted in, introduced to someone to sit with, spoken to by many people that morning.

11:27.624 --> 11:29.988
After the service, they spent time in the connect area.

11:30.228 --> 11:31.449
Then they joined Church Suite.

11:31.469 --> 11:32.591
They attended DNA.

11:32.631 --> 11:35.034
They went on to get baptized and be part of Alpha.

11:35.054 --> 11:36.656
They began serving teas and coffees.

11:36.696 --> 11:37.597
They joined a life group.

11:37.617 --> 11:38.398
They built friendships.

11:38.659 --> 11:44.306
They're now studying at Bible College and working for a Christian organization, all because someone chose to welcome

11:44.354 --> 11:51.650
Well, this year we had three amazing connect lunches out there that Christine has put on for people with her amazing team.

11:51.971 --> 11:56.942
On Christmas Day we had 40 people at the Christmas Day meal and here is a note from Christine.

11:57.684 --> 12:00.370
The Christmas meal carried deep personal meaning for me.

12:00.482 --> 12:04.047
I've known what it feels like to be alone at Christmas, missing connection and family.

12:04.368 --> 12:10.697
To now be part of creating a place where people could experience warmth, welcome and community was incredibly healing.

12:10.717 --> 12:17.748
Being able to offer that sense of family reminded me how God can redeem our painful seasons and use them to bless others.

12:18.309 --> 12:23.637
Hospitality at Skylark is not about events, it's about presence and it changes lives.

12:23.657 --> 12:27.282
So thank you Phil, Julie, Christine and everyone else who serves so beautifully.

12:27.618 --> 12:30.681
This year, we have launched four new life groups.

12:30.761 --> 12:31.561
As we said, we would.

12:31.601 --> 12:35.425
We have trained life group leaders and connected over 50 people into life groups.

12:35.445 --> 12:37.887
20 people completed the alpha course.

12:37.907 --> 12:38.968
We had five baptism.

12:39.008 --> 12:41.790
We've got another baptism on the 1st of February coming up.

12:41.810 --> 12:47.735
Our DNA courses have helped many to find out more about this amazing church family and to begin to call this place home.

12:48.216 --> 12:54.601
Our worship team has facilitated countless Sundays and brunches and breakfast collectives and counters to all of you.

12:54.701 --> 12:55.122
Thank you.

12:55.462 --> 12:57.604
Our prayer team has stood alongside hundreds

12:57.584 --> 13:00.170
of us just when we've needed it and we are grateful.

13:00.271 --> 13:01.373
Thank you to everyone.

13:01.875 --> 13:12.280
Nearly there, last page, more than 1,300 people came through the building across our three Christmas services and our online services have been watched over 11,000 times.

13:12.340 --> 13:14.706
Thank you to everybody involved in all of that.

13:14.754 --> 13:20.559
Church life team, thank you for the team who come here every month and help notices to be fun.

13:20.879 --> 13:24.362
From slides to flyers, magnets to graphics, videos to lanyards.

13:24.442 --> 13:25.583
Graphics team, thank you.

13:26.004 --> 13:29.827
From a revamp downstairs toilet, pigeon evictions.

13:30.067 --> 13:30.788
Like, could you not?

13:30.988 --> 13:32.509
We've had pigeon evictions this year.

13:32.990 --> 13:35.452
Painting maintenance and other practical upgrades.

13:36.032 --> 13:37.794
These chairs have been moved so many times.

13:37.814 --> 13:40.997
The individual chairs have been moved 13,000 times.

13:41.337 --> 13:44.740
And this room has been vacuumed so many times by people you don't

13:44.720 --> 13:45.581
even know who they are.

13:45.841 --> 13:48.804
And we are so thankful for those who served behind the scenes.

13:49.805 --> 13:58.434
We have had deeper, teach, dedications, young adults growing together in friendship, genuine connection and spiritual growth, and so much year.

13:58.474 --> 14:14.610
What a year 2025 was to every volunteer, to every leader, to every unseen servant, to those who prayed, who cooked, who lifted, who listened, who cleaned, who filmed, who cared, who served, who loved, who gave, who welcomed, who showed up.

14:14.882 --> 14:15.363
Thank you.

14:15.743 --> 14:20.070
This is what God has done among us, and we give him all the glory.

14:27.943 --> 14:32.210
If you'd like to look at the screen, you're going to see our We See A Church vision video.

15:00.194 --> 15:05.141
It's going to take you, but it's going to take too long.

15:05.181 --> 15:06.223
It's going to kill all the time.

15:06.603 --> 15:07.605
We watch it that slowly.

15:07.865 --> 15:09.988
We see a church.

15:10.108 --> 15:12.332
So I think what we may do is watch that later.

15:13.093 --> 15:16.958
And Nicky is now going to come up, if it doesn't worry, I'm sorry.

15:17.159 --> 15:18.861
It might take just a moment to get ready.

15:19.322 --> 15:27.794
Nicky's going to pop up and share with us this vision that God has downloaded to us at the start of this really important year in the life of the church.

15:32.034 --> 15:32.795
Morning everyone.

15:33.896 --> 15:34.257
Wow.

15:35.078 --> 15:36.539
Pete, firstly, well done.

15:36.579 --> 15:38.642
That was the fastest you've ever done that.

15:39.683 --> 15:42.366
It didn't feel like it lost any impact in the speed, did it?

15:42.947 --> 15:51.557
Maybe for some of us it did, but it was, it's so mind-blowing actually to see how much happens in and through the life of the church.

15:52.038 --> 15:58.866
Often we are so kind of engrossed in our own little pocket.

16:01.730 --> 16:09.666
We see a church vibrant in praise, surrendering worship and passionate about church.

16:11.069 --> 16:18.484
We see a church centered around the presence of God, ignited by the love of God, well fueled by the Word of God.

16:18.504 --> 16:21.009
I suppose I need to clarify a couple of things.

16:21.029 --> 16:23.634
When we talk about God downloading vision

16:23.810 --> 16:33.761
He's already done that and it's out in the foyer for everybody to read and we could have played the video and perhaps we'll put that out over our socials and via email just so that we can have a refresher.

16:34.181 --> 16:43.592
But if you want to know the church that we see, it is emblazoned on the walls of the foyer for everybody to read and that has not changed.

16:43.612 --> 16:47.436
So when we talk about vision, we're not changing that vision.

16:47.696 --> 16:51.881
There is still more for us to step into when it comes to that vision.

16:52.421 --> 16:53.042
But

16:54.082 --> 16:59.972
Each year, we take ourselves away in the summer and we spend time saying to God, what do you want to highlight?

17:00.133 --> 17:04.721
Which aspect of that vision are you really wanting to bring into sharp focus?

17:05.181 --> 17:08.728
Is there something fresh that you want us to catch a hold of?

17:08.948 --> 17:12.013
And this summer was no exception to that.

17:12.715 --> 17:16.882
And interestingly, this is, as Pete has already mentioned,

17:16.962 --> 17:21.410
our centenary year as a church, a hundred years since the vision began.

17:21.430 --> 17:34.194
And last week, for those of us who were here or who tapped in online, you will have seen the unfolding story that began with a woman called Rose Wibrow and currently

17:34.338 --> 17:37.661
has unfolded all the way to this point right now.

17:37.701 --> 17:47.030
And we're excited because there's a sense in which this year is a really significant one for us as a church.

17:47.070 --> 17:51.394
There's something so special and poignant about that.

17:55.998 --> 18:00.262
When we were away in the summer, God gave us the word generations.

18:01.403 --> 18:04.146
And it's easy to interpret that word

18:04.706 --> 18:06.591
as kids and youth.

18:07.413 --> 18:11.442
And we love our kids and we love our youth and you've heard so much about that this morning.

18:12.004 --> 18:21.106
But actually, as we've spent time praying and thinking and pondering about this word, generations, there's a real sense that it's broader than just that.

18:21.858 --> 18:34.070
As we stand on the cusp of this centenary year, as we get ready to celebrate, I said to the team this week, wildly, we're going to celebrate wildly in October when we hit that centenary moment.

18:34.470 --> 18:50.706
But as we step into that year, the question really is this, what could exist for generations to come at the end of the next 100 years if we collectively and individually stepped

18:50.882 --> 18:56.388
into the story that God is writing in and through this beautiful church.

18:56.868 --> 19:02.354
What legacy do we want to leave behind us for the generations coming through?

19:02.414 --> 19:10.402
And so yes, of course, our kids and our youth are a really important part of that, but we're actually thinking a century down the line.

19:10.862 --> 19:18.770
What will exist if we say our courageous yes and step wholeheartedly into the story?

19:19.042 --> 19:29.076
And we have a sense at the start of this really special year that this is more than a new vision for a new year.

19:31.519 --> 19:36.085
It's actually more than a new season which is such a churchy phrase that we use all the time.

19:36.145 --> 19:37.187
God's doing a new thing.

19:37.227 --> 19:39.049
We're often stepping into a new season.

19:39.550 --> 19:40.651
It's not even that.

19:41.733 --> 19:48.562
We have a sense that what is unfolding this year is the start of a new era.

19:48.898 --> 19:50.442
for Skylark Church.

19:51.905 --> 19:58.622
And it's been a really interesting past year, certainly from our vantage point leading the church.

19:58.983 --> 20:02.491
The headlines, as you have heard, have been so incredible.

20:02.952 --> 20:06.962
We have seen things happen this year that we could only have longed

20:07.042 --> 20:25.618
prayed for in years gone by and I think it was summed up for me in one beautiful week in the life of the church where we invited people to step into a relationship with Jesus here in the gathering and seven people responded and that same week just a few days later seven

20:25.666 --> 20:32.753
men in Chelmsford prison gave their lives to Jesus through prison alpha, and it felt like this beautiful joining up.

20:33.334 --> 20:43.244
What's happening here in the house, also happening out there in our local community as we have been faithfully sowing for years, it was exciting.

20:43.945 --> 20:45.686
So the headlines have been incredible.

20:46.487 --> 20:53.234
We've seen disciples made, our life groups have been trained and multiplied, community workers expanded,

20:53.378 --> 21:20.978
beautiful moments of symmetry we've got so much to be thankful for and yet this last year has been so intense for so many of us it feels that amidst the many blessings there have been some seismic battles we have watched and walked alongside so many key people in the life of this beautiful church family

21:21.282 --> 21:24.247
who have been facing difficult circumstances.

21:24.868 --> 21:29.154
And that's always there in a church this size, but it's felt disproportionate.

21:29.775 --> 21:46.642
There's been pain and sickness, struggle, loss, bereavement, adversity, redundancy, and some absolutely gigantic pastoral situations coexisting alongside all these incredible God headlines.

21:47.586 --> 21:51.371
And the two of us, we haven't been immune from that either.

21:52.172 --> 21:55.516
We lost Pete's dad towards the start of last year.

21:55.556 --> 21:57.139
It was February of last year.

21:57.219 --> 22:06.591
And from sort of this point last year onwards, we were back and forth to the hospital alongside juggling family life and leading a church and a network.

22:06.811 --> 22:07.592
It was full on.

22:09.034 --> 22:14.962
And we found ourselves in the heat of battle behind the scenes for most of last year.

22:15.554 --> 22:25.229
contending for some things that really matter, some things in the life of the church that need to endure that have been in danger of being lost.

22:26.170 --> 22:29.495
It's been a costly stretch, hasn't it, for so many of us.

22:30.276 --> 22:34.002
But as we have prayed and ruminated on

22:34.082 --> 22:40.870
this centenary year and this sense that there is something for us to leave for generations to come.

22:40.890 --> 22:52.004
I feel like what God has done is he's allowed us to look back on some of those more difficult parts of last year and to make sense of the struggle.

22:52.504 --> 22:56.489
Now that doesn't diminish the pain that many of us have felt this year.

22:56.950 --> 23:00.434
In any way, that doesn't go away because I'm about to say this.

23:00.546 --> 23:07.575
but it does give us a spiritual insight into why it's been such an intense time.

23:08.537 --> 23:13.343
You see, we're stepping into more than a new year at Skylop Church.

23:14.004 --> 23:15.426
It's more than a new season.

23:15.986 --> 23:18.590
It's the start of a new era.

23:19.451 --> 23:27.922
And there is a new church rising out of this existing church, a new church

23:28.226 --> 23:29.831
for a new generation.

23:30.272 --> 23:35.226
And that's why the struggle has been so intense and so strategic.

23:36.009 --> 23:43.410
Rick and Bev, who founded our network and who pasted the church, you would have seen Bev talking on the video last week.

23:44.034 --> 23:52.684
They always used to say that every seven years a new church has to rise out of the existing church.

23:52.744 --> 23:57.509
Now that doesn't mean that everything changes beyond recognition overnight.

23:57.589 --> 23:58.690
That's not what I'm saying.

23:59.311 --> 24:09.042
But there's this sense in which in order for a church to continue to grow, to continue to flourish, to not stagnate and become stale,

24:09.154 --> 24:16.884
There has to be this newness that rises, a new church that will reach a new generation.

24:16.925 --> 24:20.289
And there's something about the number seven in the Bible.

24:20.329 --> 24:21.851
It's that number of completion.

24:21.911 --> 24:24.034
It's an important number.

24:25.356 --> 24:34.508
Interestingly, this very week sees us, Peter and I step into our 14th year of leading the church.

24:35.590 --> 24:38.674
That's two lots of seven.

24:38.818 --> 24:43.103
Seven years ago, we took on leading the network.

24:43.163 --> 24:51.073
There was this sort of newness that came to us as a church family as we broadened our canopy, we broadened our mission field and horizons.

24:52.835 --> 24:57.360
But there's a sense in which there's no accident that this is that 14th year.

24:57.400 --> 25:02.787
There is a new church that needs to rise for a new generation.

25:03.448 --> 25:05.330
It's an epoch change.

25:08.354 --> 25:20.028
And perhaps in some ways that makes sense of why the battle that has led up to this point, the struggle that so many of us have felt and experienced has been so intense.

25:20.809 --> 25:34.706
Because when change is happening or about to happen, there are certain things that should come through and we have to contend for those things, but there are absolutely things that have to go as well.

25:40.770 --> 25:48.004
This new era that we are about to step into comes with a command and a promise.

25:49.427 --> 25:51.310
So here's the command, first of all.

25:51.571 --> 25:56.981
It's from Isaiah 60, verse one, and I'm reading from the amplified version on purpose.

25:58.785 --> 25:59.506
It says this.

26:00.258 --> 26:06.064
Arise, and it's actually in capital letters, which I also love because that means this is important.

26:06.625 --> 26:12.611
Arise from the depression and prostration in which circumstances have kept you.

26:13.111 --> 26:15.154
Rise to a new life.

26:15.794 --> 26:27.026
Shine, be radiant with the glory of the Lord, for your light has come, and the glory of the Lord has risen upon you.

26:29.602 --> 26:33.307
It's time, Skylark Church, for us to arise.

26:33.868 --> 26:43.902
To arise from some of those circumstances that have kept us low, that word prostration means keeping us low, keeping us limited, keeping us squashed down.

26:43.942 --> 26:47.487
And it's also time for us to shine.

26:47.547 --> 26:53.435
And this shine in this context, it's not a command to let our good deeds shine.

26:53.475 --> 26:55.858
You've just heard the list.

26:56.130 --> 26:59.915
Our good deeds definitely are shining in dark places.

26:59.975 --> 27:01.297
There's no doubt about that.

27:01.778 --> 27:04.962
But make no mistake, this command is not about that.

27:05.383 --> 27:08.147
We are great as a church at the activity.

27:08.487 --> 27:14.656
We're really good at stepping in and stepping up to the plate when it comes to serving and blessing our community.

27:14.676 --> 27:16.138
And we won't stop doing that.

27:16.779 --> 27:24.530
But this is a command to shine and be radiant with the glory of the Lord.

27:24.642 --> 27:49.068
This is a significant era that we're stepping into because our activity is going to flow in increasing measure from a radiance that only comes from time in the glory of God, the glorious presence, that extra quality that comes from each of us as we have spent time with Jesus.

27:49.149 --> 27:54.194
We're being asked to shine and be radiant with His glory

27:54.562 --> 28:11.729
And yes, the darkness may seem so very great, but this is our era to shine even more brightly with his radiant presence, the love, the peace, and the hope of Jesus, a rise and shine.

28:11.769 --> 28:19.762
To step into this brave new church that is going to arise out of our existing church,

28:20.322 --> 28:22.526
which is already super beautiful, by the way.

28:22.546 --> 28:25.391
There is nothing wrong with this beautiful church family.

28:26.653 --> 28:30.400
But in order to step into the new, something has to die.

28:30.460 --> 28:39.496
And I think that the struggle that so many of us has been in has actually been about something internally needing to die inside of us.

28:40.077 --> 28:43.263
Some of us have been in the process of dying.

28:43.363 --> 28:45.106
I don't mean actually dying.

28:45.346 --> 28:54.178
but there's been stuff that has had to die within us, old stuff that can't carry forward into the new era ahead.

28:54.898 --> 29:12.882
Now, when Peter and I met many, many years ago, now long before we were even part of this church or even dreamt that we might one day lead this church, the very first day we met, we sat under some teaching and the verse, the central verse was this,

29:13.730 --> 29:19.817
Joshua 1 verse 2, which says this, Moses, my servant, is dead.

29:19.857 --> 29:30.270
Now you, and there's this command for Joshua to lead the people from the wilderness and to cross over into the promised land.

29:33.754 --> 29:35.636
Moses, my servant, is dead.

29:35.676 --> 29:40.402
Something has to die before we can step into the next part.

29:41.154 --> 29:47.824
And when we first stepped into leading the church, one of the things that Rick and Bev prayed over us is that we were Joshua leaders.

29:48.325 --> 29:51.370
They were Moses leaders and we were to be Joshua leaders.

29:54.455 --> 30:04.050
And I feel that this is a really important threshold moment today, where there's an invitation for us, not only to step into the story,

30:04.226 --> 30:09.853
but actually to cross over into the new that God has already begun.

30:09.893 --> 30:15.319
And our job for the foreseeable is going to be to help us cross over.

30:15.339 --> 30:26.792
It's like there's a line in the sand and God is calling us to cross from the wilderness from some of those more difficult, dry places into the promised land.

30:27.333 --> 30:29.395
It's time for us to cross over.

30:30.497 --> 30:31.698
But before we do,

30:33.442 --> 30:34.283
I want to say this.

30:35.705 --> 30:39.831
It's okay to lament that which has been lost along the way.

30:39.891 --> 30:46.360
It's okay for us to grieve some of those things that we can't carry forward with us.

30:47.161 --> 30:52.489
And we've spent quite a long time during the Christmas break doing that personally.

30:52.509 --> 30:59.218
There's been a real intentional time for us of letting go of some of the disappointments

30:59.906 --> 31:09.768
the very real loss and bereavement that we experienced last year, the cumulative effect of years of sometimes painful and costly decisions.

31:10.830 --> 31:19.570
There's a unique pain and hardship that comes with leadership at times, as well as the beautiful joys and the blessings.

31:21.218 --> 31:26.085
I wonder what it is for each of us that we can't take with us into this new era.

31:26.426 --> 31:30.612
There's stuff that we need to let go of and that's going to be an ongoing process.

31:30.672 --> 31:32.775
It's not just going to happen in an instant.

31:34.337 --> 31:35.238
Moses is dead.

31:36.480 --> 31:40.466
We can't get back some of what's gone, not everything.

31:40.866 --> 31:43.509
can come forward with us into the new era.

31:43.989 --> 31:45.811
And it's time for us to step forward.

31:45.831 --> 31:49.435
And in that process, there's a letting go that has to happen.

31:49.476 --> 31:52.619
And for some of us, that might be attitudes of heart.

31:53.100 --> 31:55.803
It might be the way that we see things or do things.

31:56.283 --> 31:58.646
It could be patterns or cycles in our lives.

31:59.046 --> 32:00.688
Let's call it the old me.

32:01.869 --> 32:09.778
But some of it is also the old season, the former things, that which is good, but it's just not for now.

32:10.626 --> 32:14.390
I love that Mike Collins picked up on forget the former things.

32:14.771 --> 32:16.713
For behold, I'm doing a new thing.

32:16.753 --> 32:21.278
Whenever God is doing a new thing, he wants us to turn our gaze there.

32:22.139 --> 32:26.563
And that means forgetting the former things, letting some of those things go.

32:26.623 --> 32:29.146
They were great, but they're not for now.

32:29.186 --> 32:31.529
The winter is past.

32:31.829 --> 32:33.311
The season of singing has come.

32:34.132 --> 32:40.018
The season has changed, and it's time for us to cross over.

32:41.282 --> 32:46.790
And in Isaiah 60, verse one, that beautiful command to arise and shine.

32:46.850 --> 32:54.642
It's clear that so many of our great people in Skylar Church have been subdued by really difficult stuff.

32:55.203 --> 32:59.129
And I can't stand here and promise you that this next year won't bring hardship.

32:59.830 --> 33:02.834
I can't promise you that this next century won't be tough.

33:05.579 --> 33:10.546
But there's a choice for us to make this year and in this new era.

33:11.042 --> 33:12.624
And it's an internal choice.

33:13.666 --> 33:18.432
Will we arise from those circumstances that have kept us low?

33:18.472 --> 33:21.036
Will we stand up in the spirit?

33:21.437 --> 33:26.664
Will we arise to a new life, a renewal of our minds, our hearts?

33:27.165 --> 33:30.269
And will we choose to radiate his glory?

33:30.610 --> 33:39.442
Because we can experience hard circumstances and still radiate his glory, and so many of you do.

33:41.314 --> 33:48.262
But as we arise and as we shine, as we follow that commandment that we've been given, there is also a promise.

33:49.003 --> 33:55.250
And I just want to explain that this is not a verse that Peter and I would generally be drawn to.

33:55.811 --> 33:58.875
And initially, it might sound like a braggy verse.

33:59.435 --> 34:02.559
I just want to say, please don't receive it in that way at all.

34:03.039 --> 34:05.783
This is honestly a verse that we feel that God has given us.

34:06.263 --> 34:08.626
And it's from the book of Haggai, which is

34:08.866 --> 34:15.435
The book from which a foundational verse when the church began, what came from.

34:15.615 --> 34:20.601
And I think that the whole book of Haggai is actually really key for us in this new era.

34:20.621 --> 34:27.751
But this is what the God has spoken to us and I'll unpack in a moment what we understand by that.

34:27.811 --> 34:30.214
This beautiful promise.

34:32.317 --> 34:36.402
The glory of this present house will be greater

34:36.674 --> 34:41.041
then the glory of the former house says the Lord Almighty.

34:41.602 --> 34:47.391
And in this place, I will grant peace, declares the Lord Almighty.

34:48.212 --> 35:02.354
Listen, listening to some of those stories last week, a couple who would leave two of their children behind and travel halfway across the world to pick up a dwindling, decaying, dying church.

35:02.914 --> 35:09.881
or a woman who would look out of her window and at great cost to herself, welcome in children as a Sunday school.

35:10.241 --> 35:17.869
It's undeniable that the glory of the former house, the things that God has done have been so mind-blowing.

35:21.272 --> 35:24.335
It would be easy to think that the glory days were behind us.

35:26.257 --> 35:30.962
We can think of so many things that God has pioneered, so many highlights to date.

35:31.650 --> 35:40.748
So when this promise was whispered into our ear for our next 100 years as a church, it blew our minds.

35:41.770 --> 35:45.537
The glory days aren't behind us, Skylark Church, they're ahead of us.

35:46.018 --> 35:54.354
We haven't seen anything yet because this new church is going to be filled with his glory.

35:54.530 --> 35:58.118
Now by that we're not talking about prominence or fame.

35:58.499 --> 36:06.816
We do not aspire to be a church where people seek us out from all across the world where we are known, everybody knows our name.

36:06.836 --> 36:09.683
That's not what we're talking about here.

36:11.066 --> 36:14.994
We want to be a church that houses the glory of God.

36:15.394 --> 36:33.441
his heavy, weighty, incredible presence that changes lives, the presence that heals, restores, and transforms, the glory that strengthens people to such a degree that no matter what they face, they are still radiating his love.

36:34.001 --> 36:35.904
And that's what is meant here.

36:36.345 --> 36:39.049
The glory of the house is exactly that.

36:39.490 --> 36:42.514
It's the bit that shines out of each of us.

36:42.594 --> 36:50.165
because we have had so much time in this sustaining, good for us, life-changing, powerful presence of God.

36:51.928 --> 36:55.794
The glory that brings peace, that brings wholeness.

36:57.055 --> 37:02.083
And this is a season where we believe God is going to pour his glory into our church.

37:02.784 --> 37:12.338
And I feel that listening to that long list, there's a teeny, tiny danger that our activity could overtake

37:12.546 --> 37:17.010
our capacity and our desire to behold His glory.

37:18.914 --> 37:27.521
We don't want to become a stale, stagnating place that has loads of projects and activities, but is spiritually dry and in decline.

37:27.541 --> 37:32.125
There is a new church that must rise for a new season.

37:32.406 --> 37:36.769
We've become familiar with doing so much, and it's great.

37:37.090 --> 37:38.651
We love all the things that we do.

37:38.711 --> 37:45.957
But if we just do them because we've always done them, they lose the glory of God that is contained within.

37:46.018 --> 37:48.900
And this new era is about a pendulum

37:48.880 --> 37:56.626
that our activity will flow from his glory as opposed to the other way round.

37:58.018 --> 38:05.589
We see a church vibrant in praise, surrendered in worship and passionate about prayer.

38:05.890 --> 38:08.153
And that's the church that we want to lead.

38:08.173 --> 38:21.874
I want to lead a church that can't wait to pray because we know that God is going to answer our prayers, that he hears us, that things change when we pray, that we're changed as we pray.

38:22.018 --> 38:43.122
We want to lead a church that erupts with worship, but then carries that spirit of worship out into the way we live our lives, the way we parent our kids, the way we show integrity in our workplace, the way we reach out, roll up our sleeves and get alongside our community, the way in which we impact nations.

38:45.698 --> 38:48.281
We want to reclaim some of those things.

38:48.761 --> 38:54.488
That looks like the living, breathing, glory of God, and that we can't do.

38:54.528 --> 38:58.492
That's for all of us to do.

38:58.792 --> 39:09.304
The only way that we can host the glory of God is for every single person to climb the mountain and say, God, I want to host your presence.

39:09.624 --> 39:14.930
I want to welcome and usher in that new glory that you have for me.

39:16.066 --> 39:17.147
The season has changed.

39:17.427 --> 39:20.711
We're stepping into a new era and it's time for us to cross over.

39:21.151 --> 39:26.637
And with that, there is a call and an invitation to new passion.

39:27.899 --> 39:29.921
Many of us have lost passion.

39:30.962 --> 39:34.365
It's been eroded by our circumstances and over time.

39:35.086 --> 39:42.514
And I wonder if some of us are here today and we just feel like all we have is a tiny flickering flame.

39:43.138 --> 40:06.962
we went to retreat on retreat for a day at the start of this week and it was really funny because there's a little chapel where we went and outside the chapel they have rows of tea lights and you know when you're invited to light a candle and so Pete lit his candle from another candle and wish it went up beautifully so strong and I lit my candle

40:07.490 --> 40:11.454
And it was sputtering, and it was tiny, and it was totally pathetic.

40:11.494 --> 40:13.356
And it looked as though it was about to go out.

40:13.717 --> 40:16.860
I said, oh, Pete, that's not a good picture for the start of this year.

40:17.401 --> 40:19.223
But it's kind of how I was feeling.

40:19.243 --> 40:26.110
I felt like it was such a tough year in some ways for us that my passion had waned.

40:26.951 --> 40:31.796
I just felt, you know, when that happens to me, I'm such an enthusiastic, passionate person.

40:31.856 --> 40:32.857
You know it's bad.

40:34.058 --> 40:35.520
So I'm looking at this little candle.

40:35.600 --> 40:37.362
I'm trying to blow on it.

40:37.538 --> 40:41.282
just gently without blowing it out, but just to try and kindle something.

40:41.663 --> 40:45.928
And then Pete just gave it a jolt and boom, off it went.

40:46.709 --> 40:52.456
And we came back an hour later and I was thinking, please God, don't let my candle have gone out because that's just going to be so sad.

40:52.496 --> 40:54.358
But no, there it was.

40:54.538 --> 40:57.241
And by then it was shining equally brightly.

40:57.301 --> 41:02.708
But I think that's just a beautiful visual picture of how it's been for many of us.

41:04.089 --> 41:04.690
Yes.

41:05.058 --> 41:07.513
We need to lament that Moses is dead.

41:07.754 --> 41:12.402
There are things that have been really hard, and I am not making light of that.

41:13.058 --> 41:19.428
But God says that he won't break a bruised reed and a smoldering wick he will not snuff out.

41:19.929 --> 41:21.812
We can bring him the embers.

41:22.193 --> 41:32.229
We can bring him those bits and say, you know what, God, I've lost passion in this area as it's been tough or I've lost vision for this as it's been hard.

41:32.710 --> 41:35.935
It's okay to lament, but we can't stay there.

41:37.237 --> 41:37.778
God,

41:38.882 --> 41:50.792
We want to bring you the tiny sparks that still remain and ask for your life-giving spirit, your ruach breath to come and ignite fresh passion for a fresh season.

41:51.234 --> 41:56.146
And there's this beautiful, beautiful verse in Haggai chapter 1.

41:56.802 --> 42:03.789
The Lord is basically calling them to rebuild the house, and there's loads I could go into, but time does not permit this morning on that.

42:04.429 --> 42:11.696
But there's this moment where he calls them to rebuild the house, and then he says, God says, I am with you.

42:12.958 --> 42:17.762
And it says, so the Lord sparked the enthusiasm of Zerubbabel.

42:17.802 --> 42:25.650
He's the guy that's leading, and Jeshua, he's the high priest, and the enthusiasm of the whole remnant of God's people.

42:25.890 --> 42:29.194
they began to work on the house of their gods.

42:29.835 --> 42:32.819
And I love that idea of sparking enthusiasm.

42:33.319 --> 42:34.581
It's that thing, isn't it?

42:34.601 --> 42:35.442
It's of passion.

42:35.742 --> 42:54.386
And some translations say, God stirred up the spirit, that same Ruach breath, the life-giving spirit that caused dry bones to live, the same Ruach breath that spoke into and hovered over the void that breathed life

42:55.170 --> 42:57.874
into the dust and created mankind.

42:57.914 --> 43:08.649
The Holy Spirit wants to breathe on each of us, a fresh enthusiasm, a fresh passion for building the house, and that can only come from God.

43:09.029 --> 43:15.218
But there is a re-ignition of passion that He is wanting to inject into us.

43:29.858 --> 43:32.561
With a new era comes a new song.

43:33.663 --> 43:34.744
We are Skylarks.

43:36.486 --> 43:42.794
I sat on my own on Ears Eve, and I knew I needed to do some lamenting of my own.

43:44.096 --> 43:52.626
And to be really vulnerable with you, I spent a good few hours crying on my own with the Lord, just saying, God,

43:53.730 --> 43:57.255
There's stuff I need to let go of to be able to move in.

43:57.656 --> 44:02.223
There's so much that we can see for our church, Peter and I, that God has given us vision for.

44:05.267 --> 44:10.936
But the passion inside of me had dwindled somewhat because it's been tough and painful.

44:12.618 --> 44:15.042
And so I sat there and let all of that come out.

44:16.043 --> 44:23.314
And the one thing that I knew beyond a shadow of a doubt is that our season isn't done yet,

44:24.130 --> 44:48.434
because he's called us to raise a generation of 24, seven worshipers, those skylarks who will sing in the darkness, those skylarks who will look at the darkness and not be afraid, but look beyond to what God is doing, to sing an anthem of hope, an anthem of freedom, an anthem of peace, an anthem of healing, an anthem of worship.

44:49.570 --> 44:55.760
And until such time as we have completed that work, we have work to do.

44:55.800 --> 44:59.546
There's a new song for us to find.

45:00.227 --> 45:02.711
And last week we had different prayer stations.

45:02.751 --> 45:04.253
There was vision and passion over here.

45:04.814 --> 45:06.337
And there was 24-7 worship here.

45:06.357 --> 45:07.158
And there were two others.

45:07.599 --> 45:11.285
But I went straight over to vision and passion for the reasons that I've just outlined.

45:12.046 --> 45:14.590
And then I came over to 24-7 worship.

45:15.391 --> 45:17.234
And the coolest thing happened.

45:17.890 --> 45:40.017
As I began to pray for our church, as I began to say, you know what, God, I long for us to be a church that is so passionate about you, that we have a song, not just here on a Sunday, but in every season of our lives, through the loss, through the difficulty, through the adversity, that we hold on to that hope that we are anchored.

45:40.057 --> 45:47.826
And as I prayed, it was like, whoosh, it was just like that sputtering candle outside the chapel,

45:47.938 --> 45:53.367
I just ignited a fresh and it was this beautiful confirmation from God.

45:53.728 --> 45:55.331
Yes, this is right.

45:55.651 --> 45:57.635
There's a new song for a new season.

45:57.755 --> 45:58.957
We are Skylax.

45:59.398 --> 46:03.986
It's time to awaken the dawn with our songs.

46:05.570 --> 46:07.515
Chompsford is the birthplace of radio.

46:07.896 --> 46:14.955
You've heard us say this before, but there is a sound to be released from this place that will bless the nations.

46:15.476 --> 46:17.261
It's a sound of courage.

46:17.722 --> 46:18.986
It's a sound of truth.

46:19.387 --> 46:22.194
It's a sound of life and hope.

46:22.434 --> 46:26.840
And it's happening already through our beautiful networks, Skylark International.

46:27.181 --> 46:29.624
But there's so much more to come.

46:29.985 --> 46:36.474
We are called to raise up generations of worshipers and that work is not done yet.

46:36.855 --> 46:40.140
But we can't do it without the glory and the presence of God.

46:40.520 --> 46:46.449
We can't just have great activity, but be missing real relationship with Jesus.

46:48.732 --> 46:50.194
We've prayed our prayers.

46:50.338 --> 46:51.700
We've made our plans.

46:52.240 --> 46:55.003
If you're not in it, we don't want it.

46:55.284 --> 46:57.146
Oh God, would you move?

46:59.228 --> 47:02.532
It's interesting that the headlines today in Sky News are as follows.

47:03.453 --> 47:06.236
Why is God making a comeback with Gen Z?

47:07.457 --> 47:10.721
And why more young people are flocking to church?

47:12.123 --> 47:13.524
Right, listen.

47:15.747 --> 47:18.610
Gen Z are after an authentic

47:19.394 --> 47:20.416
encounter with God.

47:20.696 --> 47:22.258
They don't care about slick church.

47:23.060 --> 47:24.422
They don't care about any of that.

47:24.762 --> 47:27.727
They're not that interested in projects, although they'll get stuck in.

47:28.348 --> 47:40.466
The thing that they are craving is relationship and connection, firstly, vertically, and secondly, horizontally, real, meaningful, discipling community.

47:40.546 --> 47:44.269
That is the church that we want to lead into the future.

47:44.790 --> 47:47.272
It's time for a new church to rise.

47:47.652 --> 47:51.536
What are we going to leave for the next generation Skylark church?

47:51.996 --> 47:56.059
It's not about a bigger building, although maybe in time that might emerge.

47:56.360 --> 48:04.727
It's not about housing more projects and good deeds into the community, although this will likely come from spending time in the presence of God.

48:05.187 --> 48:07.609
It's bigger than the here and now.

48:08.070 --> 48:10.532
We want to raise up a generation of

48:10.512 --> 48:32.695
hearts that howls the glory of God, wherever he's placed them, hearts that howls the presence of God, that spirit of 24-7 worship that is built into the core and then released out to disciple others, the torch bearers who come are ignited and carry the flame out.

48:32.795 --> 48:34.517
Thank you for that picture, Bill.

48:34.537 --> 48:35.858
It was so powerful.

48:38.946 --> 48:56.263
a sound released from this place that will withstand hardship and pressure, which is surely only going to intensify in the times we find ourselves, and a whole-hearted spirit that will continue to worship and follow God despite the darkness.

48:57.845 --> 48:58.726
It's a new era.

49:00.868 --> 49:07.314
And last but by no means least, that era is going to lead to new life.

49:10.530 --> 49:12.352
There's an urgency over this.

49:13.413 --> 49:24.063
The church with a capital C will not survive if we don't step up to host the presence of God and pass it on to the next generations.

49:26.565 --> 49:28.647
There's new life on the horizon for us.

49:30.228 --> 49:32.911
And it looks like all of the things that we heard about and more.

49:35.894 --> 49:40.498
But there's one other thing that I want to speak about when it comes to new life

49:44.962 --> 49:54.056
Seven years ago, Peter Knight said yes to God to lead our beautiful movement, Skylark International, forward.

49:54.417 --> 49:57.442
It's a network of churches and church plants.

49:57.502 --> 50:00.587
It was pioneered from here, birthed from this very church.

50:00.647 --> 50:02.891
We planted the first church into Malden.

50:03.411 --> 50:12.626
And back then, when the network began with Rick and Bev, long before our time, everybody was on board with that because it was super costly.

50:12.834 --> 50:19.424
It was that moment of we are giving out a whole bunch of people into Malden and we've gone on to plant churches.

50:20.205 --> 50:23.931
Most recently we planted a church into Woodford with Niger, Nikki Langford.

50:23.951 --> 50:25.313
It's been part of our DNA.

50:26.915 --> 50:34.447
But over time, as we've grown as a church, we have become so good at building this church.

50:35.949 --> 50:41.938
But I wonder if at times it may have been to the detriment of that beautiful network that we

50:42.178 --> 50:43.119
gave life to.

50:44.060 --> 50:50.828
And we have found ourselves this last year, contending really strongly for the survival and the future of the network.

50:51.269 --> 50:53.131
Now that's not because it isn't growing.

50:53.772 --> 50:56.055
It's grown unrecognizably.

50:56.676 --> 50:59.098
We now have beautiful charities in our midst.

50:59.159 --> 51:00.640
We have kingdom ambassadors.

51:00.981 --> 51:02.763
We have so many ministries.

51:03.123 --> 51:08.690
We've got people who have moved their whole family into the most deprived

51:08.802 --> 51:15.512
area of Glasgow and are doing a kind of expression of church that is new and different with their whole family.

51:15.933 --> 51:26.148
We've got people in Uganda, people that you will never meet probably who are blessed because we as a church gave life to this incredible network.

51:28.171 --> 51:32.818
But as we have become so focused on local

51:33.666 --> 51:37.772
We've lost sight of our mission field, and it's been really uncomfortable this year.

51:38.153 --> 51:39.755
Peter and I wrestling with that.

51:40.636 --> 51:46.725
And I guess the only way I can describe it, and I'm very thankful to someone sitting in this room who helped us process all of this.

51:47.186 --> 51:52.854
We sat for four really strategic days to talk all of this through, and it was invaluable.

51:53.896 --> 51:55.699
But this is the only way I can describe it.

51:56.580 --> 51:58.302
This is how it looks at the moment.

51:58.983 --> 52:00.786
We've got Skylark Church here,

52:01.250 --> 52:03.673
We've got Skylark International, our network there.

52:03.693 --> 52:06.456
And there's some through flow in both directions.

52:06.476 --> 52:11.262
There are people from the church who are really invested into Skylark International, a handful of us.

52:12.003 --> 52:15.767
And occasionally we're blessed by someone coming to speak from the network here.

52:15.827 --> 52:18.290
And that's probably about as much as most of us know.

52:20.132 --> 52:21.614
But that's not how it began.

52:21.634 --> 52:25.138
And something has been lost in that.

52:26.274 --> 52:46.165
And as we prayed and processed, and as we felt this real uncomfortable thing, that this thing that began from here, that should not be lost, because it is making such a difference to hold demographics of society, we saw this picture instead.

52:47.948 --> 52:54.418
You see, here's Skylock Church, and we gave life, new life to that thing that is the network.

52:54.946 --> 52:58.009
And we will not stop investing into our local community.

52:58.069 --> 53:00.812
That is a huge part of our mission field.

53:01.473 --> 53:04.716
But we are also called to invest to the ends of the earth.

53:05.156 --> 53:10.362
And our primary vehicle for that is actually our Skylark international community.

53:10.862 --> 53:16.688
And somehow it feels as though there's this unique part of our heritage that shouldn't be lost.

53:17.329 --> 53:22.514
These concentric circles, this ripple effect,

53:23.426 --> 53:34.601
but it's hanging in the balance right now and it needs a scaffold from this church and a simulation back into our heart, into our core for it to succeed.

53:35.182 --> 53:38.727
And that is in prayer, it's in passion and it's in practical ways too.

53:40.569 --> 53:50.002
As I come into land, in 1957, there was a mission called Skylark.

53:51.138 --> 54:02.036
Britain joined the Space Race with the launch of its first rocket, and it was used by scientists to investigate Earth's upper atmosphere and carry out pioneering space research.

54:03.218 --> 54:15.218
Over 48 years, a total of 441 Skylark missions were launched, making it one of the longest and most successful rocket programs in the world.

54:16.640 --> 54:17.842
I think that's significant.

54:18.114 --> 54:27.945
You see, we are in the process of launching missions all the time into different communities across the UK and across the world, and most of us don't even know it's happening.

54:28.365 --> 54:39.958
But we see a church where Skylark is the Cape Canaveral of the network, launching new life-giving, kingdom growth initiatives across the UK and beyond.

54:40.379 --> 54:43.442
This beautiful movement that came from us

54:43.746 --> 54:51.156
assimilated once again into our hearts, into our prayer and into our missional mindset.

54:51.377 --> 55:01.791
There is new life to be released as we come into a close right now.

55:04.756 --> 55:05.236
It's time.

55:06.218 --> 55:12.146
There's a brave new church rising for a brave new generation.

55:12.258 --> 55:15.522
There's new glory for us to behold and to house.

55:15.943 --> 55:19.728
There's new passion that God is wanting to kindle in every heart.

55:20.108 --> 55:31.263
There is a new song, time for us to wake the dawn and become that generation of 24-7 worshipers for our children, our children's children and far beyond.

55:31.303 --> 55:40.114
And there is new life, both locally, nationally and internationally, that God is wanting us to steward.

55:41.890 --> 55:44.372
it's time to cross over.

55:44.973 --> 55:52.740
And I wonder if you will be part of stepping into the story with us at the start of this new era.

55:52.760 --> 55:53.421
Would you stand?

56:03.831 --> 56:06.553
Thank you for listening for such a long time.

56:06.593 --> 56:11.538
Just felt really important to share all of that with us this morning.

56:12.866 --> 56:15.349
Please do go back and have another listen when you have a move.

56:15.729 --> 56:19.373
And we will continue to unpack different strands as we move forwards.

56:19.433 --> 56:23.258
But for now, we want to give us a chance to respond.

56:24.018 --> 56:27.863
Firstly, you have a beautiful fridge magnet to take away with you.

56:27.883 --> 56:36.512
And this is, it's a poem that was found in Rose Wybrows Bible after she passed.

56:37.013 --> 56:41.778
And it feels really significant for us to have that in our homes, in our

56:41.954 --> 56:45.599
in our orbit this coming year as we step into a new era.

56:47.321 --> 56:52.088
But secondly, we'd like to invite you to respond collectively with us.

56:52.649 --> 56:55.252
We're going to do things a little bit differently this morning.

56:56.534 --> 56:58.857
