57:11.330 --> 57:15.359
There is a line of white tape, and it says, step into the story.

57:17.483 --> 57:24.418
And we're going to just form a clockwise procession for once we're better at going.

57:24.438 --> 57:24.819
It's OK.

57:25.580 --> 57:26.322
So it's just.

57:26.658 --> 57:29.061
teaching in a French classroom versus on a field.

57:30.263 --> 57:31.604
So yeah, everyone's going to move.

57:31.664 --> 57:34.848
Anyone who wants to do this is just going to make their way in that direction.

57:34.868 --> 57:36.150
So if you're here, you can go up the middle.

57:36.190 --> 57:36.731
That's fine.

57:37.171 --> 57:38.092
Come up the middle anywhere.

57:38.132 --> 57:47.544
But ultimately, to get yourselves round, if you want to step over this line, which says, I am up for it this year into this new era, I want to step into the story.

57:47.945 --> 57:49.246
When you get here, don't stop.

57:49.827 --> 57:50.548
